"{\"uid\": \"nbcphiladelphia.com-paris-2024-summer-olympics-watch-simone-biles-and-suni-lees-best-moments-from-the-womens-individual-all-around-3931054\", \"text\": \"It's the sixth straight year Team USA's women's gymnastics team has claimed gold at the Olympics individual all-around. Carly Patterson won in 2004, followed by Nastia Liukin in 2008, Gabby Douglas in 2012, Simone Biles in 2016, Sunisa Lee in 2020 and now -\\u00a0for a second time -\\u00a0Biles in 2024.  The two-time champion stunned on the vault, executing a Yurchenko double pike -\\u00a0now known as the Biles II. The move is considered the toughest vault in women's gymnastics.  Stream Philadelphia News for free, 24/7, wherever you are with NBC10.  Lee nailed her uneven bars routine, coming just behind Algeria's Kaylia's Nemour with a score of 14.866.  Though Lee wobbled on the beam, she recovered and finished cleanly.  Watch all the action from the Paris Olympic and Paralympic Games live on Peacock  And with an electric floor routine, Biles secured her second all-around gold medal, edging out Brazil's Rebeca Andrade by 1.199 points overall.\"}"